    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Expand, migrate, contract",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Add the new shape first, write both paths, backfill carefully, switch reads, then remove the old shape after you have evidence.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "migration.sql",
          "code": "ALTER TABLE subscriptions\nADD COLUMN pause_reason text;\n\n-- Backfill separately in small batches.\n-- Do not lock the world for a tidy diff.",
          "caption": "The safest migration is usually more than one deploy."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Watch the batch job",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Backfills need progress logs, retry behavior, rate limits, and a way to stop. A migration that cannot be paused is a deploy with a fuse.</p>"
        },
        {
